text: Some battle cruiser magic happening.
Old spoiler?
It is. Just one I hadn’t noticed or probably really read.

Also, that card is crazy if you get to swing with it once. It becomes a 4/4 that pumps you out 3 2/2s (in a 4 player game). Sure, it’s 6 mana, but those are some good numbers. Knight decks are looking for a top end, and this seems like a good one.
I wish they nerfed the stats and snipped that CMC down, though.
Definitely, but we already have so many smol knights
We need some big bois
It’s got a lot for 6 mana though.
and it pumps itself and with vigilance it can block well too.
And in the air
Unanswered that’s a lot of inevitability.
The other knights aren’t attacking so you’re building a wall.
Even the tokens have vigilance!
By the way, anyone other than me been thinking that the past two years or so we've started seeing more unique tribal support? Warriors more since... Tarkir, I guess, now Knights.
Vampires became big. Merfolk are back more.
Tribal is popular and probably ‘easy’ from a design sell standpoint.
Agreed, more commenting on the uniqueness of the tribes. It isn't just Elves and Goblins and Soldiers and Zombies anymore
Yup.
Thank goodness

text: Interesting
Ugh. The theme of Rowan being awful continues, I see.
I've been thinking about it since it was originally spoiled, and I can't decide how I feel about Beanstalk Giant.
Bad cultivate that also brings you a fatty in the late game seems pretty okay.
And the basic comes in untapped
I don’t hate it. Seems pretty good for an uncommon
Yeah, that's also pretty great, although its still not as good as Harrow, as is tradition.
I do kind of wish it was common, in which case it would be a Pauper EDH staple.
But meh, beggars can't be choosers.
Make it instant speed. Do you swap it for Harrow?
I don't think so, in most decks. If I'm playing lots of trample effects, maybe.
I think the thing I really like about this guy is he allows you to cheat in "Oops, All Creatures" decks, alongside [[Krosan Tusker]].

text: I've played the Beanstalk Giant on Arena a couple times. I like it a lot in the precon meta. I think it's the better balanced/mechanically sound of the currently spoiled Adventures.
Also, that swamp reminds me of Breath of the Wild.

I've had several streams of folks playing the Brawl decks on Arena and they look pretty fun, though the Knight one out of the box is a little to clunky, mostly due to mana and the commander costing 6.
Yeah, even Gavin seems like he's been down on the Mardu one. My guess is design got a hold of it and ramped the cost way up.
The knight is real dumb with the hammer though. It would be easier to deal with in non precon environments, just load up a bit more removal.
I know, I'm so mad that they took my Joust idea.
